content.text:
Notice that $\tan\theta$ can be expressed in terms of sine and cosine:
\[
\tan\theta = \frac{\text{opposite}}{\text{adjacent}} 
= \frac{\text{opposite}/\text{hypotenuse}}{\text{adjacent}/\text{hypotenuse}} 
= \frac{\sin\theta}{\cos\theta}
\]

